BidPal® Launches New Unified Platform; Event, Mobile and Online Fundraising Software









BidPal® Launches New Unified Platform; Event, Mobile and Online Fundraising Software

 0
 0

















INDIANAPOLIS — (July 25, 2017) — BidPal®, the leading mobile fundraising platform helping nonprofits raise more money and connect with more donors, is changing the face of mobile fundraising with the announcement of its 2017 Summer product release. This major software update offers fundraisers a unified platform, new user interface, enhanced functionality and more customization options than ever before. Click to Tweet.
“With BidPal’s latest release we are continuing our commitment to provide new, innovative software solutions that fit our clients’ fundraising needs. These updates further give them the freedom to focus on what truly matters—executing their organization’s mission,” said BidPal CEO Steve Johns. “Our software is easy to use yet robust, which makes it a versatile tool for any type of fundraising event; and most importantly, helps nonprofits save valuable time.”
The all new platform was built to make fundraising easier and to further increase donor engagement. The seamless interface responds to fit any device—from desktop computer to tablet to smart phone—and enables donors to use a global login (email, Facebook or Google credentials) for every event.
Nonprofits now also have flexible mobile ticketing for fundraising events. The new guest profile section enables supporters to edit contact and payment information at any point. Additionally, this release enables nonprofits to further communicate with their supporters via text message using BidPal’s annual software subscription.
“The new design and donor experience is something we are very excited about,” said Mike Wilkinson, deputy director of events at Human Rights Campaign. “The product continues to deliver and keeps us on the forefront of technology for our donors today.”
The unified platform also contains several enhanced features for nonprofits, including a completely customizable menu that allows nonprofits to rename default options, turn options on and off, reorder lists, highlight sponsors, and create additional custom fundraising pages.
“I love the new design and overall enhanced experience for our donors,” said Kristy Thomas, director of special events at St. Ursula Villa in Cincinnati. “It is super user friendly and seamless across all mobile devices.”
To support the new platform, BidPal offers industry-leading services, including onsite event management, account management, as well as phone and email support. A preview of the product is available at https://www.bidpal.com/one-test-drive/.
The 2017 Summer product release is immediately available.
 
About BidPal, Inc.
BidPal creates user-friendly fundraising software that helps nonprofits engage donors, raise more money and save valuable time and resources. Our cloud-based mobile and payment solutions have helped thousands of organizations raise more than $1 billion through 10,000 events and connect with over one million unique donors. Located in the marketing technology hub of Indianapolis, BidPal has been recognized on the Inc. 500 list of Fastest Growing Companies and has received a Techpoint MIRA award for Mobile Technology Excellence & Innovation. Connect with us on Facebook at Twitter.
